{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775852613567,"sessionID":"ses_286f28ce6ffep8ntWwTGOpmVoB","part":{"id":"prt_d79106f390014P9cRVukaaT7pq","messageID":"msg_d790e698a0013qFam4L7dvOAC9","sessionID":"ses_286f28ce6ffep8ntWwTGOpmVoB","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-13bd8cfee6bf4627ae04742ac2c42eea","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-011/design.md","content":"# AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发 Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发 |\n| Module | `pkg/router` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\nThe Router JWT module provides token-based authentication for secure communication between Router and sandbox pods. It handles JWT token generation (signing), verification (validation), key management, and integration with the reverse proxy for Authorization header injection.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### System Context\n\n```\n┌─────────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐\n│   Client SDK    │────▶│     Router      │────▶│   Sandbox Pod   │\n│ (Python/CLI)    │     │  (pkg/router)   │     │ (with picod)    │\n└─────────────────┘     └─────────────────┘     └─────────────────┘\n                               │                         │\n                               │                         │\n                               ▼                         ▼\n                         ┌─────────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐\n                         │   JWT Manager   │     │   Kubernetes    │\n                         │ (RS256 keys)    │     │   Secret Store  │\n                         └─────────────────┘     └─────────────────┘\n```\n\n### JWT Token Flow\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    JWT Generation Flow                               │\n│                                                                      │\n│  1. Request arrives at handleInvoke (server.go)                     │\n│     └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐       │\n│                                                               │       │\n│  2. SessionManager.GetSandboxBySession → SandboxInfo         │       │\n│     └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤       │\n│                                                               │       │\n│  3. Check kind == SandboxKind or SandboxClaimKind            │       │\n│     └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤       │\n│                                                               │       │\n│  4. JWTManager.GenerateToken(claims)                         │       │\n│     ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐     │       │\n│     │  Claims:                                         │     │       │\n│     │  - session_id: sandbox.SessionID                 │     │       │\n│     │  - sandbox_id: sandbox.SandboxID                 │     │       │\n│     │  - namespace: sandbox.SandboxNamespace           │     │       │\n│     │  - name: sandbox.SandboxName                     │     │       │\n│     │  - exp: now + 5min                               │     │       │\n│     │  - iat: now                                      │     │       │\n│     │  - iss: \"agentcube-router\"                       │     │       │\n│     └─────────────────────────────────────────────────┘     │       │\n│                                                               │       │\n│  5. RS256 Signing (rsa.PrivateKey)                           │       │\n│     └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤       │\n│                                                               │       │\n│  6. ReverseProxyWrapper.Director                             │       │\n│     └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤       │\n│     │  req.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer \"+jwt)        │       │\n│                                                               │       │\n│  7. Request forwarded to sandbox pod                         │       │\n│     └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘       │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### JWT Verification Flow (Future Enhancement)\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    JWT Verification Middleware                       │\n│                                                                      │\n│  HTTP Request with Authorization header                              │\n│        │                                                             │\n│        ▼                                                             │\n│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │ JWTAuthMiddleware                                             │   │\n│  │  ┌────────────────┐  ┌────────────────┐  ┌────────────────┐  │   │\n│  │  │   Extract      │──│   Parse        │──│   Validate     │  │   │\n│  │  │   Token        │  │   Claims       │  │   Signature    │  │   │\n│  │  └────────────────┘  └────────────────┘  └────────────────┘  │   │\n│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n│        │                                                             │\n│        ▼                                                             │\n│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │ Claim Extraction → context.Set(\"session_id\", ...)             │   │\n│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n│        │                                                             │\n│        ▼                                                             │\n│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │ Handler proceeds with authenticated context                    │   │\n│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n---\n\n## Design\n\n### Component Relationships\n\n| Component | Role | Dependencies |\n|-----------|------|--------------|\n| `JWTManager` | RS256 key generation, token signing, key persistence | `rsa.PrivateKey`, Kubernetes client (optional) |\n| `JWTConfig` | JWT configuration (expiration, issuer, algorithm) | None |\n| `JWTAuthMiddleware` | Token verification middleware (future) | `JWTManager` |\n| `TokenRefresher` | Token refresh handler (future) | `JWTManager` |\n| `KeyManager` | Key persistence to Kubernetes Secret | `JWTManager`, Kubernetes client |\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Package | Purpose | Import Path |\n|---------|---------|-------------|\n| golang-jwt | JWT token generation and parsing | `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` |\n| crypto/rsa | RSA key generation and signing | Go standard library |\n| crypto/x509 | Key serialization (PKCS1, PKIX) | Go standard library |\n| encoding/pem | PEM encoding for key storage | Go standard library |\n| crypto/rand | Secure random key generation | Go standard library |\n| Kubernetes client | Secret persistence (optional) | `k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes` |\n| Klog | Logging | `k8s.io/klog/v2` |\n\n---\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### JWTManager (`jwt.go`)\n\n```go\ntype JWTManager struct {\n    privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey  // 2048-bit RSA private key for signing\n    publicKey  *rsa.PublicKey   // Derived public key for verification\n    k8sClient  kubernetes.Interface  // Optional: for secret persistence\n}\n\nconst (\n    rsaKeySize         = 2048                 // RSA key size in bits\n    jwtExpiration      = 5 * time.Minute      // Default token expiration\n    IdentitySecretName = \"picod-router-identity\"  // Kubernetes Secret name\n    PrivateKeyDataKey  = \"private.pem\"        // Secret data key for private key\n    PublicKeyDataKey   = \"public.pem\"         // Secret data key for public key\n)\n\nvar IdentityNamespace = \"default\"  // Overridden by AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE env\n```\n\n### JWTConfig (Future Enhancement)\n\n```go\ntype JWTConfig struct {\n    Algorithm      string        // \"RS256\" (default) or \"HS256\"\n    TokenExpiry    time.Duration // Default: 5 minutes\n    RefreshExpiry  time.Duration // Default: 30 minutes (for refresh tokens)\n    Issuer         string        // Default: \"agentcube-router\"\n    Audience       []string      // Optional audience claim\n    ClockSkew      time.Duration // Allowed clock skew for validation\n}\n```\n\n### JWT Claims Structure\n\n```go\ntype RouterClaims struct {\n    SessionID  string `json:\"session_id\"`  // Unique session identifier\n    SandboxID  string `json:\"sandbox_id\"`  // Sandbox pod identifier\n    Namespace  string `json:\"namespace\"`   // Kubernetes namespace\n    Name       string `json:\"name\"`        // Sandbox name\n    jwt.RegisteredClaims\n}\n\ntype RegisteredClaims struct {\n    ExpiresAt *jwt.NumericDate `json:\"exp,omitempty\"`  // Expiration timestamp\n    IssuedAt  *jwt.NumericDate `json:\"iat,omitempty\"`  // Issued at timestamp\n    NotBefore *jwt.NumericDate `json:\"nbf,omitempty\"`  // Not valid before\n    Issuer    string           `json:\"iss,omitempty\"`  // \"agentcube-router\"\n    Subject   string           `json:\"sub,omitempty\"`  // Optional subject\n    Audience  ClaimStrings     `json:\"aud,omitempty\"`  // Optional audience\n    ID        string           `json:\"jti,omitempty\"`  // JWT ID (unique)\n}\n```\n\n### TokenPair (Future Enhancement)\n\n```go\ntype TokenPair struct {\n    AccessToken  string `json:\"access_token\"`   // Short-lived token (5 min)\n    RefreshToken string `json:\"refresh_token\"`  // Long-lived token (30 min)\n    ExpiresIn    int64  `json:\"expires_in\"`     // Seconds until expiration\n    TokenType    string `json:\"token_type\"`     // Always \"Bearer\"\n}\n```\n\n### Key Persistence Types\n\n```go\ntype KeySecret struct {\n    Name      string            // Secret name: \"picod-router-identity\"\n    Namespace string            // Namespace from AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\n    Data      map[string][]byte // \"private.pem\" and \"public.pem\" keys\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### Existing: Token Generation (Internal)\n\nToken generation is performed internally during reverse proxy routing:\n\n```go\nfunc (j *JWTManager) GenerateToken(claims map[string]interface{}) (string, error)\n```\n\n**Generated Claims:**\n```json\n{\n  \"exp\": 1703001234,\n  \"iat\": 1703000934,\n  \"iss\": \"agentcube-router\",\n  \"session_id\": \"sess-abc123\",\n  \"sandbox_id\": \"sbx-xyz789\",\n  \"namespace\": \"default\",\n  \"name\": \"my-agent-runtime\"\n}\n```\n\n### Future: Token Issuance Endpoint\n\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| POST | `/auth/token` | Issue new access/refresh token pair |\n| POST | `/auth/refresh` | Refresh access token using refresh token |\n| GET | `/auth/public-key` | Retrieve public key for verification |\n\n### Token Issuance Request/Response\n\n```go\ntype TokenRequest struct {\n    UserID   string                 `json:\"user_id\"`    // User identifier\n    Roles    []string               `json:\"roles,omitempty\"`  // Role claims\n    Metadata map[string]interface{} `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`  // Custom claims\n}\n\ntype TokenResponse struct {\n    AccessToken  string `json:\"access_token\"`   // JWT access token\n    RefreshToken string `json:\"refresh_token\"`  // JWT refresh token\n    ExpiresIn    int64  `json:\"expires_in\"`     // Expiration in seconds\n    TokenType    string `json:\"token_type\"`     // \"Bearer\"\n}\n\ntype RefreshRequest struct {\n    RefreshToken string `json:\"refresh_token\"`  // Valid refresh token\n}\n\ntype PublicKeyResponse struct {\n    PublicKey string `json:\"public_key\"`  // PEM-encoded public key\n    Algorithm string `json:\"algorithm\"`   // \"RS256\"\n    Issuer    string `json:\"issuer\"`      // \"agentcube-router\"\n}\n```\n\n### Middleware Integration\n\n```go\ntype JWTAuthMiddlewareConfig struct {\n    SkipPaths      []string      // Paths to skip auth (e.g., \"/health/*\")\n    TokenExtractor TokenExtractor // Custom token extraction function\n    KeyFunc        jwt.Keyfunc   // Key lookup function\n}\n\ntype TokenExtractor func(r *http.Request) (string, error)\n\nfunc DefaultTokenExtractor(r *http.Request) (string, error) {\n    authHeader := r.Header.Get(\"Authorization\")\n    if authHeader == \"\" {\n        return \"\", ErrTokenMissing\n    }\n    parts := strings.Split(authHeader, \" \")\n    if len(parts) != 2 || parts[0] != \"Bearer\" {\n        return \"\", ErrTokenInvalidFormat\n    }\n    return parts[1], nil\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Key Management\n\n### Key Generation Strategy\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    Key Lifecycle                                     │\n│                                                                      │\n│  1. Router Startup                                                   │\n│     └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐       │\n│                                                               │       │\n│  2. Check Kubernetes Secret existence                        │       │\n│     ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐     │       │\n│     │  k8sClient.CoreV1().Secrets().Get(ctx, name)     │     │       │\n│     └─────────────────────────────────────────────────┘     │       │\n│                                                               │       │\n│  3a. Secret exists → Load existing keys                      │       │\n│      ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │       │\n│      │  loadPrivateKeyPEM(secret.Data[\"private.pem\"])   │    │       │\n│      │  publicKey = &privateKey.PublicKey               │    │       │\n│      └─────────────────────────────────────────────────┘    │       │\n│                                                               │       │\n│  3b. Secret not exists → Generate new keys                   │       │\n│      ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │       │\n│      │  rsa.GenerateKey(rand.Reader, 2048)              │    │       │\n│      │  encodePrivateKeyPEM, encodePublicKeyPEM         │    │       │\n│      └─────────────────────────────────────────────────┘    │       │\n│                                                               │       │\n│  4. Store keys in Kubernetes Secret                          │       │\n│     ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐     │       │\n│     │  k8sClient.CoreV1().Secrets().Create(ctx, secret)│     │       │\n│     └─────────────────────────────────────────────────┘     │       │\n│                                                               │       │\n│  5. JWTManager ready for token operations                    │       │\n│     └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘       │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### PEM Encoding Functions\n\n```go\nfunc encodePrivateKeyPEM(key *rsa.PrivateKey) []byte {\n    return pem.EncodeToMemory(&pem.Block{\n        Type:  \"RSA PRIVATE KEY\",\n        Bytes: x509.MarshalPKCS1PrivateKey(key),\n    })\n}\n\nfunc encodePublicKeyPEM(key *rsa.PublicKey) []byte {\n    bytes, err := x509.MarshalPKIXPublicKey(key)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil\n    }\n    return pem.EncodeToMemory(&pem.Block{\n        Type:  \"PUBLIC KEY\",\n        Bytes: bytes,\n    })\n}\n\nfunc loadPrivateKeyPEM(data []byte) (*rsa.PrivateKey, error) {\n    block, _ := pem.Decode(data)\n    if block == nil {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to decode PEM block\")\n    }\n    return x509.ParsePKCS1PrivateKey(block.Bytes)\n}\n```\n\n### Secret Structure\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: v1\nkind: Secret\nmetadata:\n  name: picod-router-identity\n  namespace: ${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE:-default}\ntype: Opaque\ndata:\n  private.pem: <base64-encoded RSA private key>\n  public.pem: <base64-encoded RSA public key>\n```\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Custom Error Types (`errors.go`)\n\n| Error Type | HTTP Status | Code | Message | Condition |\n|------------|-------------|------|---------|-----------|\n| `JWTSigningError` | 500 | `JWT_SIGNING_FAILED` | \"jwt signing failed\" | Token signing failure |\n| `JWTValidationError` | 401 | `JWT_VALIDATION_FAILED` | \"jwt validation failed\" | Token verification failure |\n| `JWTTokenExpiredError` | 401 | `JWT_TOKEN_EXPIRED` | \"jwt token expired\" | Token past expiration |\n| `JWTTokenMissingError` | 401 | `JWT_TOKEN_MISSING` | \"jwt token missing\" | No Authorization header |\n| `JWTInvalidFormatError` | 401 | `JWT_INVALID_FORMAT` | \"invalid authorization header format\" | Malformed header |\n| `JWTKeyLoadError` | 500 | `JWT_KEY_LOAD_FAILED` | \"jwt key load failed\" | Key loading failure |\n\n### Error Type Definitions\n\n```go\ntype JWTSigningError struct {\n    Err error\n}\n\nfunc (e *JWTSigningError) Error() string {\n    return \"jwt signing failed: \" + e.Err.Error()\n}\n\nfunc (e *JWTSigningError) Status() int { return 500 }\nfunc (e *JWTSigningError) Code() string { return \"JWT_SIGNING_FAILED\" }\nfunc (e *JWTSigningError) Message() string { return \"jwt signing failed\" }\n\ntype JWTTokenExpiredError struct {\n    TokenID string\n}\n\nfunc (e *JWTTokenExpiredError) Error() string {\n    return \"jwt token expired: \" + e.TokenID\n}\n\nfunc (e *JWTTokenExpiredError) Status() int { return 401 }\nfunc (e *JWTTokenExpiredError) Code() string { return \"JWT_TOKEN_EXPIRED\" }\nfunc (e *JWTTokenExpiredError) Message() string { return \"jwt token expired\" }\n```\n\n### Error Response Format\n\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"<message>\",\n  \"code\": \"<error code>\"\n}\n```\n\n### JWT Parsing Errors Mapping\n\n| jwt.Parse Error | Router Error |\n|------------------|--------------|\n| `jwt.ErrTokenExpired` | `JWTTokenExpiredError` |\n| `jwt.ErrTokenSignatureInvalid` | `JWTValidationError` |\n| `jwt.ErrTokenMalformed` | `JWTValidationError` |\n| `jwt.ErrTokenNotValidYet` | `JWTValidationError` |\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Test Coverage Goals\n\n| Component | Coverage Target | Key Test Cases |\n|-----------|-----------------|----------------|\n| `jwt.go` | 80%+ | Key generation, token signing, claim merging, expiration, PEM encoding/decoding |\n| `middleware.go` (auth) | 90%+ | Token extraction, validation flow, error responses, path skipping |\n| `KeyManager` | 85%+ | Secret creation, key loading, key rotation |\n\n### Unit Tests (`jwt_test.go`)\n\n| Test | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `TestNewJWTManager` | Verify RSA key generation (2048-bit) |\n| `TestJWTManagerGenerateToken` | Token generation with custom claims, verify claims present |\n| `TestJWTManagerTokenExpiration` | Verify exp claim is approximately 5 minutes from now |\n| `TestJWTManagerGetPublicKey` | Verify public key retrieval for verification |\n| `TestEncodePrivateKeyPEM` | PEM encoding contains \"RSA PRIVATE KEY\" |\n| `TestEncodePublicKeyPEM` | PEM encoding contains \"PUBLIC KEY\" |\n| `TestLoadPrivateKeyPEM` | Load PEM data back to RSA key, verify key equality |\n| `TestLoadPrivateKeyPEMInvalid` | Invalid PEM data returns error |\n| `TestJWTSigningError` | Error type methods (Error, Status, Code, Message) |\n\n### Integration Test Scenarios\n\n| Scenario | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| Key persistence | Generate → Store in K8s Secret → Restart → Load existing keys |\n| Token flow | Generate token → Verify with public key → Extract claims |\n| Proxy integration | Request → JWT generated → Authorization header set → Forwarded |\n| Secret namespace | AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE env override for Secret location |\n\n### Test Utilities\n\n```go\ntype MockJWTManager struct {\n    GenerateFunc func(claims map[string]interface{}) (string, error)\n    VerifyFunc   func(tokenString string) (*RouterClaims, error)\n    PublicKey    *rsa.PublicKey\n}\n\ntype MockKeyManager struct {\n    StoreFunc  func(ctx context.Context, privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey) error\n    LoadFunc   func(ctx context.Context) (*rsa.PrivateKey, error)\n    ExistsFunc func(ctx context.Context) (bool, error)\n}\n```\n\n### Benchmarks\n\n```go\nfunc BenchmarkJWTGenerateToken(b *testing.B) {\n    jwtMgr, _ := NewJWTManager()\n    claims := map[string]interface{}{\n        \"session_id\": \"test-session\",\n        \"sandbox_id\": \"test-sandbox\",\n    }\n    b.ResetTimer()\n    for i := 0; i < b.N; i++ {\n        jwtMgr.GenerateToken(claims)\n    }\n}\n\nfunc BenchmarkJWTVerifyToken(b *testing.B) {\n    // Measure token verification performance\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Checklist\n\n- [x] `JWTManager` struct with RSA 2048-bit key pair\n- [x] `GenerateToken(claims)` method with RS256 signing\n- [x] Standard claims: exp (5min), iat, iss (\"agentcube-router\")\n- [x] PEM encoding functions for private/public keys\n- [x] `GetPublicKey()` method for verification\n- [x] `JWTSigningError` custom error type\n- [ ] `ValidateToken(tokenString)` method for verification\n- [ ] `JWTAuthMiddleware` for incoming request authentication\n- [ ] Key persistence to Kubernetes Secret\n- [ ] Key rotation support\n- [ ] Token refresh endpoint\n- [ ] Public key distribution endpoint\n- [ ] Clock skew tolerance configuration\n\n---\n\n## Validation Rules\n\n1. RSA key size must be 2048 bits (minimum for RS256 security)\n2. Token expiration defaults to 5 minutes (short-lived for sandbox communication)\n3. Issuer claim must be \"agentcube-router\" (hardcoded)\n4. Private key stored in PKCS1 PEM format\n5. Public key stored in PKIX PEM format\n6. Secret name: `picod-router-identity`\n7. Namespace: `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` env or `default`\n\n---\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n### Key Storage\n- Private key stored in Kubernetes Secret (base64 encoded)\n- Secret should be mounted only in Router pod\n- Consider using sealed secrets for GitOps deployments\n\n### Token Lifetime\n- Access tokens expire in 5 minutes (short-lived)\n- Tokens are single-use per request (forwarded to sandbox)\n- No token caching in Router\n\n### Algorithm Security\n- RS256 preferred over HS256 (asymmetric, verifiable without secret)\n- Private key never shared with sandbox pods\n- Public key can be distributed to verification endpoints\n\n### Key Rotation\n- Generate new keys: `rsa.GenerateKey(rand.Reader, 2048)`\n- Store new keys in Secret with versioned name\n- Sandbox pods need updated public key for verification\n\n---\n\n## Open Questions\n\n1. **Token Blacklist**: Should revoked sessions invalidate tokens immediately?\n   - Current: Tokens expire naturally after 5 minutes\n   - Alternative: Redis-backed blacklist for immediate revocation\n\n2. **Multi-tenancy**: Should different namespaces use different keys?\n   - Current: Single key pair for all namespaces\n   - Alternative: Per-namespace key secrets\n\n3. **Key Rotation Strategy**: When and how should keys rotate?\n   - Current: Keys generated once at startup\n   - Alternative: Scheduled rotation (weekly/monthly) with overlap period\n\n4. **Token Audience**: Should tokens include audience claim?\n   - Current: No audience restriction\n   - Alternative: `aud: [\"sandbox-pod\"]` for target verification\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- `jwt.go` — Current JWT implementation\n- `server.go:154-171` — Token generation in handleInvoke\n- `reverse_proxy.go:41-43` — Authorization header injection\n- `errors.go:63-81` — JWTSigningError definition\n- `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go` — AuthModeType constants\n- [RFC 7519 — JSON Web Token (JWT)](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7519)\n- [RFC 7518 — JSON Web Algorithms (JWA)](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7518)\n- [golang-jwt/jwt v5](https://github.com/golang-jwt/jwt)"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/router/middleware.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/router/server.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":156,"character":52},"end":{"line":156,"character":63}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#any"},"source":"any","message":"interface{} can be replaced by any"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/router/session_manager.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/router/config.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/router/doc.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":26,"character":33},"end":{"line":26,"character":44}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#any"},"source":"any","message":"interface{} can be replaced by any"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/router/errors.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/router/jwt.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":49,"character":53},"end":{"line":49,"character":64}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#any"},"source":"any","message":"interface{} can be replaced by any"},{"range":{"start":{"line":59,"character":2},"end":{"line":59,"character":16}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#mapsloop"},"source":"mapsloop","message":"Replace m[k]=v loop with maps.Copy"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T16